pesticide.PPE: Long-sleeved shirt and long pants; Shoes plus socks; For aerial applications, mixers and loaders must also wear: Chemical-resistant gloves made of barrier laminate, butyl rubber ≥14 mils, nitrile rubber ≥14 mils, neoprene rubber ≥14 mils, natural rubber ≥14 mils, polyethylene, polyvinyl chloride (PVC) ≥14 mils, or Viton™ ≥14 mils

Active_Ingredients.name: Trinexapac-ethyl
Active_Ingredients.mode_Of_Action: Inhibiting the production of gibberellic acid

Safety_Information.general_Info: Have the product container or label with you when calling a poison control center or doctor, or going for treatment. For 24-Hour Medical Emergency Assistance (Human or Animal) or Chemical Emergency Assistance (Spill, Leak, Fire, or Accident), Call 1-800-888-8372.

Application_Info.max_product_per_acre_per_season: 7.0 fl oz (0.11 lb ai) per acre per year
